item.description:
fixed: <p>
The <code>register_post_type_args</code> (and <code>register_taxonomy_args</code>) filter has been available since WordPress 4.4 (see <a class="closed ticket" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/17447" title="#17447: enhancement: Add 'register_post_type_args' hook (closed: fixed)">#17447</a>). As mentioned above, the default post types <em>are</em> re-registered on the <code>init</code> hook, so these filters also apply to default post types and taxonomies.
</p>
<p>
Example usage:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">add_filter( 'register_post_type_args', function( array $args, $name ) {
	if ( 'post' === $name ) {
		$args['labels']['menu_name'] = 'News';
	}
	return $args;
}, 10, 2 );
</pre><p>
Please feel free to re-open if something about these filters is not working as expected.
</p>

